Sonneratia apetala

    Authority   Ham.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Myrtales:Sonneratiaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names kambala, pagapat, pagapato, mangrove
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 9938

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   A small to medium sized evergreen tree
   GROWING PERIOD
   Fast-growing perennial.
   COMMON NAMES
   Keora, Kandal, Kylanki, Marama, Kanbala.
   FURTHER INF
   Keora occur in tidal forests of India, Bangladesh and Myanmar. It is
   often found on new alluvial land thrown up in the form of islands or
   flats in the bends of tidal rivers. Yearly yields may be about 30
   m3/ha. (pH estimated by the compiler).

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Zabala N 1990 pp 84-86 [TEMP, RAIN, TEXT, DRA, LIG, USE]
   Troup R 1921 pp 608-609 [USE, TEXT]
   National RC 1983c [DRA, SAL, TEXT, TEMP, KTMP, RAIN, DEP]

